CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1958, pg. B2, reads: "Entranced by Nature - Some of the guests of the 30th annual outing, which the James East Liberty Missionary Society of Ebenezer Baptist Church sponsored at Highland Park recently, reflect outdoor magic. Seated, left to right, they are Misses Dolly Johnson, Jennie Reed, Mmes. Dicey Dean, Virginia Dickerson and Josephine King.  Standing clockwise: Mmes. Louise Williams, Lettie Harris, Miss Lena Johnson and Mrs. Louise Pendleton."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of elderly women, seated from left: Dolly Johnson, Jennie Reed, Dicey Dean, Virginia Dickerson, and Josephine King; standing: Louise Williams, Lettie Harris, Lena Johnson, and Louise Pendleton, posed around bench in Highland Park for 30th annual outing of James East Liberty Missionary Society of Ebenezer Baptist Church
